Text.Value: Only Wulbren couldn't leave the stories be - so he went and bloody found it. A small supply, tucked away down here with a manuscript.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wulbren is his charismatic leader

Text.Value: You really would, wouldn't you? But not us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sizing you up again - you've acted selflessly thus far and he's a little in awe - but he can't share you idealism

Text.Value: Surely you can do me a little more honour than that.
There's little we can do to stop them from here, I'm afraid. We have our own freedom to look to.

EditorData.NodeContext: His people are still enslaved - he needs to be pragmatic.

Text.Value: If it's truly that powerful, then we can't let the cult have it.
Maybe Wulbren can hold out. Either way, he's beyond our help now.
As for Wulbren... we can only hope they'll make his end swift.
Wulbren knew the risks when he came in search of runepowder. We all did.
Beldron - I was so worried! Did Nere hurt you?

EditorData.logicalname: Sided Nere, but killed him, Lunkbug available

Text.Value: We'll all be free yet. The Ironhands always find a way.
My people will find somewhere to regroup across the lake. Then on to the city.
Who's Wulbren?
No, no - I'm all right. Did the sergeant hurt you?
I try not to need saving. Hasn't much worked out, as you can see.

EditorData.NodeContext: Self-deprecating

Text.Value: You say you're grateful - but my coinpurse is still light.
Then we'll just have to free him first.
I've had fights enough for one day, Barcus.
If my path takes me to Moonrise, I'll see about freeing Wulbren myself.
I also like to know things. Start talking.
Glittering gods. I should've know that one was too damn stubborn to die.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tone of fond respect

EditorData.logicalname: Gnomes still slaves, Player tried to free them, Lunkbug available

Text.Value: And he was bloody right. He found it - a small cache sitting down here with a manuscript.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some of his weariness melting away - he's seasoned, but still capable of feeling wonder when a myth is proved true

Text.Value: We have our own freedom to look to, I'm afraid. We'll take our chance when it arises, then back to the city.

EditorData.NodeContext: His people are still enslaved - he needs to be pragmatic.

Text.Value: Beldron - thank Ironhand!

EditorData.logicalname: Sided Nere, but killed him, Lunkbug available

Text.Value: We ought to thank someone a little closer by, I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tired, wry - referencing the player when his husband thanks the gods

Text.Value: If you knew half as much as you think, my lad, Wulbren might have kept you around.

EditorData.NodeContext: Again, talking down to Barcus. He pities him more than dislikes him

Text.Value: It doesn't matter. We can't help him from here.
He'd just made sense of the formula when the cult jumped us - so he burned the damn thing.

EditorData.NodeContext: Revealing Wulbren did something nigh-on sacreligious

Text.Value: I'm taking the rest of us 'cross the lake. Safer shores and all that.
Gaerdal Ironhand you may not be, but you damn well fight like him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Impressed with you - someone thanked the war-god Ironhand and he's implying you're the next best thing

Text.Value: Thank Thulla - she's the one who set me on your trail.
Aye. The explosive of Gaerdal Ironhand's own creation. Fistfuls wiping out armies, all those old stories.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confirming and pressing on, as if knwoing you'll disbelieve him and understanding why. Tone is 'Yes I know it's crazy, but true'

Text.Value: That business is what sent us after the powder to begin with. Now... we'll have to make other arrangements.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, tired - thinking of a long struggle ahead

Text.Value: Business that sent us after the powder to begin with. The formula might be gone, but we still have the barrels.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, tired - thinking of a long struggle ahead

Text.Value: I'm grateful, don't mistake me, but... why help us? You're one of them, aren't you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Guarded, sizing the player up - he thinks we're one of the cultists

Text.Value: What has he gotten himself mixed up in now...
Aye. The cult kept us for slave-hands, but Wulbren was our leader. He... knows things.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant to say exactly what Wulbren knows

Text.Value: And neither will this twit, apparently.
That didn't much look like begging. But no complaints from me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referencing the player's recent slaughter of his captors

Text.Value: If you're talking about runepowder, Philomeen already blew it up. And herself with it.
Taken to Moonrise Towers. The rest of us were set digging, but... Wulbren knows things. Seems the cult wants to know them too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant to say exactly what Wulbren knows

EditorData.logicalname: Killed rebels and Nere, Lunkbug navailable

Text.Value: Make it quick! We need to find Wulbren - now.
Run away, then. I have my own business to be about.
I wouldn't trust them with a bloody butter knife. But it's a fight for another day.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snorting, derisive

Text.Value: ... they could flatten the whole of the Sword Coast.
Fah. Thought I'd have to breathe my last in Nere's stink.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grateful. Breathless.
EditorData.logicalname: Sided Nere, but killed him, Lunkbug unavailable
Killed Nere and rebels, Lunkbug unavailable

Text.Value: And yet the cult didn't clap you in chains. I'd like to learn that trick.
Aye. Nor us, I'm afraid.

EditorData.NodeContext: shrugging, a little defeated. This line trails off into another 'Much as I want to march after Wulbren myself... we can't.'

Text.Value: Before you ask, no - I'm not going to stage a rescue.
This is no time to be coy. What is that Wulbren knows?
Not long enough.

EditorData.NodeContext: Blunt

Text.Value: I've lost so much. Please, just - just let me be.
You know what to do.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Beldron returns to normal position and speaking tone.
EditorData.NodeContext: Beldron returns to normal position and speaking tone.

Text.Value: And just like that, you'd leave Wulbren behind. I knew you lot were foolish, but I didn't know you were cruel.
We're done here.
The leader of our expedition. He was sent off to Moonrise Towers.
You did just lift a mountain from our heads, so... good enough for me, I reckon.

EditorData.NodeContext: Nodding, accepting - not going to look a gift horse in the mouth

Text.Value: It is. And if the pick swung the other way, I'd expect Wulbren to do the same.

EditorData.NodeContext: Acknowledging he's leaving his friend behind -

Text.Value: EXPLAIN. QUICKLY.
Start explaining, or I start breaking bones.
Then we're of one mind, I think.
Would this have anything to do with runepowder?
The cult thinks it owns me. I beg to differ.
Freedom. Or what passes for it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thrilled to be released, with a deep breath.

Text.Value: What?!

EditorData.NodeContext: Shock

Text.Value: Here - the Ironhand Gnomes honour their debts. With Wulbren gone, that falls to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Drawing himself up to perform a necessary obligation - doesn't see himself as leadership material but accepts the responsibility

Text.Value: He'd admire your resolve. And your optimism.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thinks the player's idealism is misplaced, but won't stand in their way

Text.Value: Wulbren has a way of attracting true believers - his quest for runepowder was the latest dream he stuffed in our heads.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry, but with a hint of weariness - Beldron believes in the cause, but he knew Wulbren in his youth, before he became a charismatic figure the other gnomes idolise

Text.Value: You're a little late, Barcus my lad. He's already been sent to Moonrise Towers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slight tone shift - he and Barcus have been at odds before. Beldron speaks down to Barcus VERY slighttly

Text.Value: You're just abandoning your leader? That's cold.
You. Thank you for trying to free us, at least. I thought you were with the cult.

EditorData.NodeContext: Turning to player - still grim at his people's continuing status as slaves, but grateful that you TRIED to do something.

Text.Value: If you find yourself in Baldur's Gate, seek us out. We'll raise a glass to Wulbren together.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bidding you farewell

Text.Value: Spare the secrecy. Philomeen already escaped with the runepowder.
Things the cult would like to know too, it seems.
Wulbren's been taken to Moonrise Towers, I hear.
No, I'm one of you.

EditorData.logicalname: Nere or duergar freed gnomes, Lunkbug available

Text.Value: ... then it seems you've saved us twice over. Gods above - she bloody did it. Of course she did.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mute astonishment - a friend of his managed to escape the slavers and bring some runepowder with her

Text.Value: No. Debt's a stone 'round your neck, and we Ironhands like to walk tall. We'll be fine.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gently firm - too proud not to give you a reward

Text.Value: Do the right thing. Kill Nere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Leaning in and whispering

Text.Value: I don't plan on being anywhere nearby when they do.
I'd rather not think about it. Besides, we have our own freedom to look to.

EditorData.NodeContext: His people are still enslaved - he needs to be pragmatic.

Text.Value: ... a sad end. But a fitting one for a true believer. When Wulbren claimed that runepowder existed, she was the first to volunteer.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mute grief, but not shock - an older man unsurprised by the fanaticism of the youths in his group

Text.Value: We'll be leaving soon enough.
Are you always so suspicious of those who save you?
I'm all right, I promise. I just wish...
We were just slave-hands to the cult, but not Wulbren. He... knows things. Things they want to know too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitant to say exactly what Wulbren knows

Text.Value: Thought we'd leapt from frying pan to flame for a moment, there.
Wise, I think. Losing our leader is a blow, but we have our own freedom to look to.

EditorData.NodeContext: His people are still enslaved - he needs to be pragmatic.

Text.Value: My people can barely stand. And we have business back in the city.

EditorData.NodeContext: Pragmatic - mentally moving on from the thought of saving Wulbren

Text.Value: If there's a single copy left, it's sitting in his head. Those Absolutists pull it out and make runepowder...

EditorData.NodeContext: Ominous - the cult are likely to torture Wulbren for what he knows

Text.Value: I know someone looking for this Wulbren. Where is he?
Who cares? We're together now, thank Ironhand!

EditorData.AnimationTags: gnomes embrace, and then pull apart.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to Beldron. The two gnomes embrace, and then pull apart.

Text.Value: You came through. I can't believe it. I owe you more than you know.

EditorData.logicalname: Killed duergar and Nere after keeping gnomes enslaved

Text.Value: How long do you think he can hold out?
You'll call me mad, but... fine. Wulbren's found the formula for runepowder.

EditorData.NodeContext: Considering a moment - then shrugging - 'what does he have to lose'

Text.Value: Keep the coin. It seems like you'll need it.
It would seem not.
Enough. Bickering won't save your friend.
But not Wulbren. He bloody found it - a small cache, buried down here with a manuscript.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wonder/awe at his leader's perserverance

Text.Value: We'll be safer 'cross the Ebonlake. Then back to the city, Gaerdal Ironhand willing.

EditorData.NodeContext: GAIR-dul EYE-urn-hnd

Text.Value: ... I know. I do too. But we're together - that's what matters.
How did you... well, you're a sharp one. Most still believe it's a fairy tale - I know I did, once.

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised at how much you know, then deciding to spill the whole story

Text.Value: I wish I could. But most of our funds rested with our leader, Wulbren. He'll be in Moonrise Towers by now.
Whatever the cult wants, I want the opposite. We need to free your friend.
It's Wulbren I'm worried for. He was sent on to Moonrise Towers.

Synopsis: The gnome leader's main dialogue. He thanks you for saving them, and tells you what brought his people to the Underdark to begin with - an expedition led by their charismatic leader Wulbren, to find a forgotten gnomish explosive of awesome power - runepowder.
